![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/65cde49a-2902-40cd-9a11-37484f3948be/373.jpg?format=original)

In this episode of the _Major Issues Podcast_, the hosts dive into _Daredevil: Dark Art_ (2016), the chilling second arc of Charles Soule’s _Daredevil_ run. When a twisted new villain named Muse starts leaving behind grotesque "art" made from his victims, Matt Murdock and his protégé Blindspot find themselves in a race against time to stop a psychopath who sees murder as his masterpiece. With striking visuals, high-stakes action, and a gripping moral dilemma, this arc puts Daredevil to the test like never before. Join us as we break down the story, the themes, and why Muse might be one of Daredevil’s creepiest foes yet!

Please leave us a **_review_** on [**ITunes**](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience and grow as podcasters! Rate us wherever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our merchandise! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by **ComicBook Clique**, the only stop for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media.

